<h1>Tableless don't bite</h1>
<p>
Everyday I see more people interested in Tableless; I've received e-mails with questions about advantages and disadvantages, doubts of people that are beginning or just curious to know more about this method.
In the other hand, many people are still mistrustfully, they think that are more disadvantages than advantages, or that some limitations can afect the web layout creations.
</p>
<p>
More and More, sites with contents are adhering to Tableless, we have this examples: ESPN (www.espn.com), FastCompany (www.fastcompany.com), American Megatrends (www.ami.com).
Tableless isn't a seven head dragon, isn't a thing that you don't know if its Works or not. To make a tableless site, you just need to know HTML, CSS, and have a layout, nothing from another world.
</p>

<h1>Freedom of Creation</h1>
<p>
Many people say that Tableless puts a limit in your layouts creation 
Yeah, tableless has some limitations, and it can't deny it, in example : I was implementing the Web Insider's web site (www.webinsider.com.br), when I was almost finishing, I encountered a problem: the tables of right side of the site, they finished together, Independent of the content size of each table, if you want to take a look at: <a href="http://www.tableless.com.br/webinsider/">http://www.tableless.com.br/webinsider/</a>.
</p>
<p>
A problem that I didn't has with tables, and a limitation of TableLess. But this problem seems to being solved, you can check it out here. 
In other hand, in spite of this little limitation, with tableless you have freedom of creativity, easiness that wouldn't have with tables, in example of this easiness: Do a Layout with one side in curve, check it out: http://www.meyerweb.com/eric/css/edge/curvelicious/demo.html 
To creating your layouts, look for know the methods, read more about CSS and HTML. Use Your Creativity for abuse of advantages (that are lot of times bigger than disadvantages). 
Let's to Know About it
What can I Say for you that is in the beginning, is try it, learn it, you have nothing to loose learning tableless….  O que eu posso dizer para você que está iniciando, é que experimente, aprenda, você não vai perder nada aprendendo... Start slowly, do in tables the things you can't do only using css, after that, very slowly, left tables behind.
What can happen is that you don't like it, and keeping use the old (overshot) tables. 
I finish with a Quote of Elesbão e Haroldinho, for those people who make bad judgment about tableless, but even try it: "they justify the failure with technical limitation, but are few cases that this argument is true. They update their Software, but don't update their heads. The Problem isn't the fake ability, inexistent merit, an attitude that doesn't reflect in execution.   The Ideal is to reflect about own ego, and make oneself to learn and learn a lot of things…" Design De Bolso nº8 
